Shipping Tycoon Fredriksen Tops Norway Rich List, Kapital Says

-- B y   M e e r a   B h a t i a
-- 
2011-09-23T06:00:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-23/shipping-tycoon-fredriksen-tops-norway-rich-list-kapital-says.html
John Fredriksen , the owner of
supertankers and oil rigs, remained the richest person in  Norway 
this year after his wealth dropped 0.5 percent to 59.7 billion
kroner ($10.2 billion), an annual list by Kapital magazine
showed.  Fredriksen, 67, who became a citizen of Cyprus five years
ago, is the largest shareholder in  Seadrill Ltd. (SDRL) , an offshore
oil rig company, oil-tanker company Frontline Ltd. as well as
 Marine Harvest ASA (MHG) , the worldâ€™s biggest salmon farmer.  Olav Thon, the 88-year-old real estate developer, came in
second after his wealth rose to 23.9 billion kroner from 21.3
billion kroner in 2010. He controls Olav Thon Eiendomsselskap
ASA. Odd Reitan, 60, who owns Norwegian wholesaler and retail
franchiser Reitangruppen AS together with other family members,
moved up to third place with 23.4 billion kroner, up from 19
billion kroner, Kapital said.    To contact the editor responsible for this story:
